.RS -4
.B
Note:
.RE
Note that the compiler may optimize away atoms\&. For example, the compiler will rewrite \fIatom_to_list(some_atom)\fR\& to \fI"some_atom"\fR\&\&. If that expression is the only mention of the atom \fIsome_atom\fR\& in the containing module, the atom will not be created when the module is loaded, and a subsequent call to \fIbinary_to_existing_atom(<<"some_atom">>, utf8)\fR\& will fail\&.

