.TP 2
*
If option \fIcompact\fR\& is specified, the trailing zeros at the end of the list are truncated\&. This option is only meaningful together with option \fIdecimals\fR\&\&.
.LP
.TP 2
*
If option \fIscientific\fR\& is specified, the float is formatted using scientific notation with \fIDecimals\fR\& digits of precision\&.
.LP
.TP 2
*
If \fIOptions\fR\& is \fI[]\fR\&, the function behaves as \fB\fIfloat_to_list/1\fR\&\fR\&\&.
.LP
.RE

.LP
Examples:
.LP
.nf

> float_to_list(7\&.12, [{decimals, 4}])\&.
"7.1200"
> float_to_list(7\&.12, [{decimals, 4}, compact])\&.
"7.12"
.fi
.RE
.LP
.nf

