.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
GroupLeader = Pid = pid()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Sets the group leader of \fIPid\fR\& to \fIGroupLeader\fR\&\&. Typically, this is used when a process started from a certain shell is to have another group leader than \fIinit\fR\&\&.
.LP
The group leader should be rarely changed in applications with a supervision tree, because OTP assumes the group leader of their processes is their application master\&.
.LP
See also \fB\fIgroup_leader/0\fR\&\fR\& and \fBOTP design principles\fR\& related to starting and stopping applications\&.
.RE
