.br
                        bitstring() | [])
.fi
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Returns a bitstring that is made from the integers and bitstrings in \fIBitstringList\fR\&\&. (The last tail in \fIBitstringList\fR\& is allowed to be a bitstring\&.) Example:
.LP
.nf

> Bin1 = <<1,2,3>>\&.
<<1,2,3>>
> Bin2 = <<4,5>>\&.
<<4,5>>
> Bin3 = <<6,7:4>>\&.
<<6,7:4>>
> list_to_bitstring([Bin1,1,[2,3,Bin2],4|Bin3])\&.
<<1,2,3,1,2,3,4,5,4,6,7:4>>
.fi
