.nf
\fBmax_heap_size()\fR\& = 
.br
    integer() >= 0 |
.br
    #{size => integer() >= 0,
.br
      kill => boolean(),
.br
      error_logger => boolean()}
.fi
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
This flag sets the maximum heap size for the calling process\&. If \fIMaxHeapSize\fR\& is an integer, the system default values for \fIkill\fR\& and \fIerror_logger\fR\& are used\&.
.RS 2
.TP 2
.B
\fIsize\fR\&:
The maximum size in words of the process\&. If set to zero, the heap size limit is disabled\&. \fIbadarg\fR\& is be thrown if the value is smaller than \fB\fImin_heap_size\fR\&\fR\&\&. The size check is only done when a garbage collection is triggered\&.
.RS 2
.LP
\fIsize\fR\& is the entire heap of the process when garbage collection is triggered\&. This includes all generational heaps, the process stack, any \fB messages that are considered to be part of the heap\fR\&, and any extra memory that the garbage collector needs during collection\&.
.RE
.RS 2
.LP
\fIsize\fR\& is the same as can be retrieved using \fB\fIerlang:process_info(Pid, total_heap_size)\fR\&\fR\&, or by adding \fIheap_block_size\fR\&, \fIold_heap_block_size\fR\& and \fImbuf_size\fR\& from \fB\fIerlang:process_info(Pid, garbage_collection_info)\fR\&\fR\&\&.
.RE
.TP 2
.B
\fIkill\fR\&:
When set to \fItrue\fR\&, the runtime system sends an untrappable exit signal with reason \fIkill\fR\& to the process if the maximum heap size is reached\&. The garbage collection that triggered the \fIkill\fR\& is not completed, instead the process exits as soon as possible\&. When set to \fIfalse\fR\&, no exit signal is sent to the process, instead it continues executing\&.
.RS 2
.LP
If \fIkill\fR\& is not defined in the map, the system default will be used\&. The default system default is \fItrue\fR\&\&. It can be changed by either option \fB+hmaxk\fR\& in \fIerl(1)\fR\&, or \fB\fIerlang:system_flag(max_heap_size, MaxHeapSize)\fR\&\fR\&\&.
.RE
.TP 2
.B
\fIerror_logger\fR\&:
When set to \fItrue\fR\&, the runtime system logs an error event via \fB\fIlogger\fR\&\fR\&, containing details about the process when the maximum heap size is reached\&. One log event is sent each time the limit is reached\&.
.RS 2
.LP
If \fIerror_logger\fR\& is not defined in the map, the system default is used\&. The default system default is \fItrue\fR\&\&. It can be changed by either the option \fB+hmaxel\fR\& int \fIerl(1)\fR\&, or \fB\fIerlang:system_flag(max_heap_size, MaxHeapSize)\fR\&\fR\&\&.
.RE
.RE
.LP
The heap size of a process is quite hard to predict, especially the amount of memory that is used during the garbage collection\&. When contemplating using this option, it is recommended to first run it in production with \fIkill\fR\& set to \fIfalse\fR\& and inspect the log events to see what the normal peak sizes of the processes in the system is and then tune the value accordingly\&.
.RE
.LP
.nf

.B
process_flag(Flag :: message_queue_data, MQD) -> OldMQD
.br
.fi
